# bhcom-ba (Angular 21)

Logistics SPA with **employee** (`/`) and **admin** (`/admin`) portals. Prefer existing abstractions over new UI frameworks.

## App structure (`src/app/`)

Only three top-level folders ‚Äî no `core/`, `features/`, or `layout/`:

| Folder | Role |
|--------|------|
| `shared/` | Auth, i18n, theme, `constants/`, `form/`, `table/`, `confirm/`, `ui/` ‚Äî used by guest and portal |
| `guest/` | Public routes, guest shell, guest guards, login/register pages |
| `portal/` | Authenticated shell, configs, guards, features, `pages/page-placeholder/` |

Paths below are relative to `src/app/` unless prefixed with `src/`.

## Import boundaries

- `shared/**` ‚Äî import anywhere (guest + portal).
- `guest/**` ‚Üí imports `shared/**` only (URLs via `shared/constants/app-urls.ts`). Do not import portal configs or features.
- `portal/employee/**` ‚Üî `portal/admin/**` ‚Äî **no** cross-import of features or routes.
- Feature HTTP: colocate `*.service.ts` in the feature; promote to `portal/{employee|admin}/data/` when shared within one portal.

## Commands

- `npm start` ‚Äî dev server (4200)
- `npm run build` ‚Äî production build
- `npm test` ‚Äî run existing Vitest suite only when asked; see **Testing** below

## Testing (agents)

- **Never add unit tests** ‚Äî no new `*.spec.ts` files, Vitest cases, test helpers, or test-only dependencies.
- Do not scaffold, suggest, or include unit tests as part of feature work, refactors, or bug fixes unless the user explicitly requests tests.
- Do not extend or rewrite existing unit tests unless the user explicitly asks.
- Prefer manual verification (`npm start`, `npm run build`) over adding coverage.

## Source map (read files when implementing, don‚Äôt guess)

- Root routes: `app.routes.ts` ‚Äî guest routes + lazy portal trees with `portalMatchGuard`
- Guest routes: `guest/guest.routes.ts`
- Portal routes: `portal/employee/employee.routes.ts`, `portal/admin/admin.routes.ts`
- App URLs + portal kind: `shared/constants/app-urls.ts`, `shared/constants/portal-kind.type.ts` ‚Äî **never hardcode route paths**; see `.cursor/rules/app-urls.mdc`
- Auth: `shared/core/auth/` ‚Äî session types (`AuthUser`, `Session` in `auth.model.ts`); stub login until API; company registration stub in `guest/pages/register/register-company.service.ts`
- Guards: `guest/guards/guest.guard.ts` (`guestGuard`); `portal/guards/portal-match.guard.ts`
- Portal config: `portal/common/models/portal-config.model.ts`, `portal/employee/employee-portal.config.ts`, `portal/admin/admin-portal.config.ts`
- Portal shell: `portal/shell/` ‚Äî `PortalShellComponent`, `PortalSidebarComponent`, `PortalTopbarComponent`, `shared.sidebar.service.ts`
- Sidebar nav: `portal/employee/employee-nav.config.ts`, `portal/admin/admin-nav.config.ts` (types in `portal/common/models/nav.model.ts`)
- Theme/i18n: `shared/core/theme/`, `shared/core/i18n/`
- Forms: `shared/form/` (barrel `index.ts`); Tables: `shared/table/` (barrel `index.ts`); Confirm: `shared/confirm/` (`ConfirmService`, global `ConfirmDialogComponent` in `app.html`)
- Features: `portal/employee/features/` (fleet, shipments); `portal/admin/features/` (vehicles)
- Placeholder pages: `portal/pages/page-placeholder/page-placeholder.component.ts`
- i18n: `public/assets/en.json` + `bh.json`
- Theme/breakpoints: `src/styles.scss`, `src/styles/_breakpoints.scss`, `portal/shell/viewport.ts`

## Auth routing (guards)

| Guard | Where | Behavior |
|-------|-------|----------|
| `guestGuard` | `/`, `/sign-in`, `/login`, `/register`, `/admin/login` | Unauthenticated ‚Üí allow; authenticated ‚Üí session portal home |
| `portalMatchGuard` | `''` and `admin` lazy trees | Unauthenticated ‚Üí `/`; wrong portal ‚Üí correct portal home |

## Layout behavior (do not reimplement ad hoc)

- **Desktop:** persistent sidebar (`SidebarService.collapsed`), panel collapse/expand in brand row.
- **Mobile (‚â§768px):** topbar hamburger ‚Üí drawer; brand shows portal suffix + close (X).
- **Main scroll:** `.portal-shell__content` (portal) or guest shell outlet area (guest).

